article.headline: Glover sparks 66-61 comeback win for Mount St. Mary's
article.linkText: Glover sparks 66-61 comeback win for Mount St. Mary's
article.story: EMMITSBURG, Md. -- Junior Robinson led with 21 points and Charles Glover came off the bench to score nine in the final 8:30 as Mount St. Mary's chewed through a 10-point deficit to beat Saint Francis (Pa.) in a come-from-behind 66-61 win on Saturday. Mount St. Mary's (12-15, 9-5 Northeast Conference) trailed 49-39 when Glover started the comeback with a pair of free throws followed by unanswered 3-pointers from Gregory Graves and BK Ashe. Glover added a 3-pointer and a layup as Mount St. Mary's closed to 56-54 as part of a 13-2 run with Saint Francis going scoreless for nearly six minutes. Robinson scored his final five points from the foul line. Saint Francis (13-12, 9-5) had a four-game win streak end. Ronnie Drinnon scored 11 points and grabbed 20 rebounds for the second time in three games. Ben Millaud-Meunier, who's closing on 1,000 points, was held to five on 1-for-9 shooting.
